description.0: Dude Jensen’s demonic transformation into Roulette leaves Roxanne pressed to the wall and fighting for her life. Ghost Rider arrives with a last-minute rescue, but by then, Satan’s been involved…
description.1: Trouble down under! The Cobalt Man is destroying Sydney with his nuclear powers! Can Betty and Ted free Bruce from his tranquilized captivity?
description.2: Golden armor! Raw courage! Smashing fists! Can anything stand against the fury of the Freak? Find out as Iron Man faces his deadliest foe yet!
description.3: Thor and Hercules team up to take down Pluto! Will Krista be delivered from Hades? But before Thor and Herc can face the God of the Underworld, they must first battle Ares, God of War!
description.4: Rachel Van Helsing and Dracula are trapped together in the mountains - forced to rely on each other to survive!
description.5: Morbius, genetically engineered vampire, is on the prowl AGAIN!
description.6: The Human Torch and Medusa are stranded in the Himalayas! But before they can figure out how they can survive, they're in for the fight of their lives against the savage Ternak!
description.9: Spider-Man uncovers the truth behind Doc Ock's interest in Aunt May. Just before Spidey can interrupt the wedding between sworn enemy and beloved aunt, Hammerhead's lackeys arrive on the scene. Will Spider-Man be able to save the most important woman in his life?
description.10: After Taurus launches the Avengers and his Zodiac cartel into space, the two super-powered groups must combine forces to return to Earth's orbit.
description.11: Captain America and the Falcon fall prey to the deafening screams of the Banshee!
description.15: Tara reveals her true nature to Morbius, showing off her super-powered psychic abilities! Morbius faces a conflict in conscience.
description.17: Dr. Vault uses his power to summon Fin Fang Foom!
description.19: Doctor Strange's journey through time continues!
description.20: Wundarr plunges into the ocean and Namorita must save him, but gets scared off when Namor arrives. Then the Dakkams send a giant robot to destroy Wundarr and the Thing and his allies must protect him.
description.23: Stegron makes a mess of the Savage Land and Ka-Zar is none to happy about it. Maybe Spidey can lend him a hand!
description.25: Hulk becomes a stowaway on Ralph Robert's ship on a mission to test an H-bomb. The Cobalt Man reveals himself to the X-Men.
description.27: Olympus and Asgard get ready to rumble, as Thor confronts Hercules over Krista's fate! But will the characteristically arrogant Herc be open to Thor's demands? Not a chance, True Believer!
description.28: A battle of the monsters! Dracula is still on the run from vampire hunters, but can even he escape the feral fury of the WEREWOLF?
description.29: The board is set - thus Doom makes his move! Before the FF can fully recover from his last attack, Doom unleashes a new evil to destory them - a deadly android known only as the Seeker!
description.35: The First Appearance of the Spider-Buggy!  Spider-Man faces threats from multiple places...at the same time! Hammerhead, Doctor Octopus, and the newly-minted Jackal, prove Spidey's toughest opposition yet.
description.36: The Avengers trace the Zodiac death-ray to the World Trade Center, but the battle ends abruptly when Mantis nearly falls to her death. Cornelius Van Lunt, a.k.a Taurus, meets with his Zodiac compatriots and devises a new plan that will destroy the Avengers.
description.37: Cap's in jail and accused of murder! He's been set up by the malicious committee to regain America's principles and its super-figurehead, Moonstone-and Cap's unable to prove his innocence! Plus, the Falcon gets new wings!
description.38: Thanos uses the power of the Cosmic Cube to kidnap Captain Marvel, Moondragon, Drax, and Iron Man. Will the heroes be able to overcome Thanos with their combined might?
description.39: DAREDEVIL RETURNS TO NEW YORK! Soon after his return to the city, Daredevil learns that Foggy has been investigating a group called "Black Spectre". Black Widow guest-stars!
description.42: The first issue starring Morbius the Living Vampire! Now a vagrant wandering the streets of Los Angeles, Morbius is reminded of his eternal condition after feasting on a young woman.
description.45: When Xemnu the Titan takes out the Hulk, it's up to the might of the Defenders to defeat the alien menace.
description.49: Kraven the Hunter sets his sights on capturing Zabu!
description.51: Blastaar blasts out of the Negative Zone and it's up to the Human Torch and the Hulk to contain him!
description.53: A gig at Dude Jensen’s Demolition Derby turns into an opportunity for Ghost Rider to exact justice against Red Thompson’s would-be killers! Linda Littletrees puts the moves on Johnny, causing Roxanne to take some distance…
description.54: In an attempt to send Hulk into a space-time warp, Dr. Corbeau releases the Juggernaut from his interstellar exile...and places him in the same cage as the Green Goliath!
description.55: Iron Man continues his rampage, this time going up against the mighty Thor, god of thunder! It's titan versus titan! Avenger versus Avenger! Who will win?
description.57: Thor has never faced foes like these before! The Masters of the Black Stars easily overtake our hero- what's a Thunder God to do when his divine powers prove useless?
description.58: Blade and Dracula - Round Two! Can the world's greatest vampire hunter defeat the world's greatest vampire?
description.59: Satana stumbles upon a satanic cult that may pave the way to a meeting with her father!
description.60: The return of the FF's greatest ever nemesis is at hand - DOOM is coming! And with the FF still splintered like never before, the maniacal monarch might very well destroy them once and for all!
description.66: First Appearance of the Punisher!  The Jackal has hired someone to take out Spider-Man, which puts Spidey in the crosshairs of Frank Castle, the Punisher!
description.67: The Gemini twins of the Zodiac use their joint powers to create a death-ray that will kill every NYC citizen born under a specific star sign. The Avengers must stop the Zodiac crime cartel before it's too late.
description.68: The Star-Spangled Avenger finds himself on the other side of the law in this issue! Find out why Captain America is a wanted criminal!
description.69: Daredevil and Black Widow are aided by Captain Marvel in the final battle against Terrex!
description.70: Trapped in the 18th century! Doctor Strange and Baron Mordo have been stranded in the past, and must fight for their lives against Sise-Neg, dark sorcerer of the distant future!
description.74: Mole Man and his Moloids terrorize Spidey and Mr. Fantastic!
description.76: The Hulkbuster base has been captured by Abomination and the Rhino, and the villains have Jack Armbruster, Colonel Ross and Betty as their captives!
description.78: What dwarfs the God of Thunder in both size and power? The Masters of the Black Stars align themselves against Asgardian invaders...
description.79: Dracula has finally met his match! Can even the legendary vampire defeat a man who REFUSES TO DIE?
description.80: Reed is left a broken leader after rendering his infant son comatose, breaking up his family and the Fantastic Four. Only Medusa remains with Mister Fantastic, since she understands why he had to hurt Franklin. Meanwhile, Ben waits nervously by Alicia's side before an operation that will restore her eyesight...
description.82: Spider-Man uses his last reserve of webbing after being dropped from the sky by Vulture! After narrowly avoiding death, Spidey returns to ESU's campus to uncover the motives behind an innocent woman's death. In a twisted web of mistaken identities, will Spider-Man solve this murder mystery before there's a second victim?
description.83: The Avengers end up at a dangerous Halloween party where they are kidnapped by their host, Tom Fagan. Fagan is actually the Collector, a galactic super-villain who wants to acquire the "earthling" heroes as part of his museum of oddities. Meanwhile, Black Panther and Mantis find time to bond.
description.84: Captain America may be a trained gymnast, but he's no match for the Tumbler! Plus, find out why the Falcon and the Black Panther meet in secrecy when a legend dies!
description.85: The Controller returns! Will Captain Marvel be able to triumph over his foe this time?
description.90: PANTHER'S RAGE PART 3: Black Panther fends off Malice when she attacks the palace in an attempt to free her ally Venomm! Contains only the "Malice By Crimson Moonlight" story.
description.93: Moondragon has been gravely injured! Can Daredevil save her before it's too late?
description.96: An ancient Kree weapon unites Spider-Man and Captain Marvel to stop the pending destruction!
description.97: The Defenders are sent back to the time of the Crusades, where Black Knight has been fighting for King Richard. But they now have a new enemy: an army of Gnomes!
description.99: With his Spirit of Vengeance dwindling, Johnny Blaze races through the night to save Roxanne from Big Daddy Dawson. Upon their return to Earth, Witch-Woman teaches Ghost Rider a new trick.

7.text: The origin of the Sons of the Tiger.  The amulets that Black Tiger, Bob Diamond and Lin Sun possess allow them to unlock the power of the tiger and avenge their fallen master. Note: this issue only contains the Sons of the Tiger story.

12.text: Luke begins to discover that those he loves the most are in peril.

13.text: Shang Chi confronts Sir Denis about Black Jack Tarr and the evil Fu Manchu's scheming!

16.text: The Foolkiller’s origins revealed, as well as his past ties to Richard Rory. Why is Foolkiller so intolerant of ‘sinfulness’? Man-Thing takes a life, and the swamp’s balance is restored.

17.text: Dr. Vault uses his power to summon Fin Fang Foom!

18.text: The Hunchback of Notre Dame has Topaz held captive in the bell tower of the famed Paris cathedral!

19.text: Doctor Strange's journey through time continues!

20.text: Wundarr plunges into the ocean and Namorita must save him, but gets scared off when Namor arrives. Then the Dakkams send a giant robot to destroy Wundarr and the Thing and his allies must protect him.

22.text: Namor's brutal brawl with Force continues! But this time, the Sub-Mariner does not fight alone! Guest-starring the AMAZING SPIDER-MAN!

24.text: Gateway University is in need of an exorcist, and there's no one better for the job than Daimon Hellstrom!

31.text: The Monster threatens to give in to his bestial nature, despite pleas for mercy from innocent villagers. Has Count Dracula sated his thirst? Young gypsy Carmen is at risk of being the vampire’s next meal, but Frankenstein’s Monster has other plans!

32.text: Co-starring the Foolkiller! Foolkiller is hot on Man-Thing’s trail- but why? Richard and Ruth find love with each other, while F.A. Schist and Hargood strengthen their plot against Man-Thing. Plus, a daring rescue from the mouths of angry alligators!

33.text: The unusual history of Rattack! Plus, the Martians now have Killraven in custody -- but his public execution may elevate him to martyrdom…

34.text: Dracula is on a mission to retrieve a book belonging to Baron Russoff, and will go through Jack to have it!

40.text: KA-ZAR and SHANNA aren't too keen on the idea of becoming human sacrifices. But when a triceratops rampages through their village, the Fall People are convinced Ka-Zar's blasphemy is to blame!

45.text: When Xemnu the Titan takes out the Hulk, it's up to the might of the Defenders to defeat the alien menace.

47.text: Howard the Duck’s first appearance! The Nexus of All Realities has been disturbed, and Jennifer Kale’s dreams portend a dark future. A barbarian named Korrek is launched into our dimension through a jar of peanut butter. You may be laughing now, but you won’t be by the end of this issue!

48.text: Young Richard Rory is down on his luck after facing a gator attack in the Florida swamps. But his innocence grants him the protection of Man-Thing! F. A. Schist advances his plan of building an airport- a plan that involves the destruction of Man-Thing.

49.text: Kraven the Hunter sets his sights on capturing Zabu!

50.text: Jack and Topaz return Phillip Russell’s mind back to him, and later fight Taboo and Algon!

52.text: Loralee is kidnapped by the Cult of the Darklord! After they’ve attacked Brother Voodoo!

62.text: Luke Cage comes up with his super hero moniker -- Sweet Christmas, it’s Power Man!

63.text: Shang-Chi reunites with M'Nai, an old friend, but the circumstances are less than ideal -- M'Nai has been ordered by Fu Manchu to assassinate Shang-Chi!

70.text: Trapped in the 18th century! Doctor Strange and Baron Mordo have been stranded in the past, and must fight for their lives against Sise-Neg, dark sorcerer of the distant future!

71.text: Man-Thing vs. The Thing! Ben Grimm takes a side trek to Florida after discovering a swampy menace is using a name similar to his own. It’s a battle for the ‘Thingdom’, as the muck monster and Ever Lovin' Blue Eyed Grimm go head-to-head! But when Molecule Man makes an appearance, will these two set aside their differences?

73.text: ATLANTIS DEVASTATED! The fate of his entire people rests in Namor's hands, and he'll have to do the unthinkable to save them! But first he'll have to survive the attack of the villain known only as FORCE!

75.text: Daimon Hellstrom is determined to defeat his evil father once and for all, but his investigation leads him to find answers about himself instead! Witness the true origin and destiny of the Son of Satan!

86.text: While guarding the Nexus of All Realties, Marvel’s resident muck-man encounters an overeager duck from Duckworld, and Korrek the Barbarian! Will this unlikely trio be able to save the time stream from the likes of Thog the Nether-Spawn?

87.text: The two most horrifying creatures in English literature, head-to-head! Frankenstein’s Monster vs. Count Dracula! Or are they on the same team? The Lord of Vampires must feed, and a nearby village is on the menu.

88.text: Jack gets unexpected help while kidnapped by Taboo!

89.text: The son of an English nobleman, KA-ZAR grew up in the Savage Land alongside his loyal tiger Zabu after the death of his parents. Read his unbelievable origin here!

90.text: Contains only the "Malice By Crimson Moonlight" story. PANTHER’S RAGE PART 3: Black Panther fends off Malice when she attacks the palace in an attempt to free her ally Venomm!

92.text: While on a mission in Washington, D.C., Killraven and his men become merchandise in an alien slave market!

98.text: Brother Voodoo heads back to Haiti to uncover the mysterious source of roving Zuvembies!
